BACKGROUND AND OBJECTIVES

BACKGROUND

The current PAN-OS version on the Palo Alto PA-850 deployed at BUT Mubadala Energy (Sebuku) Ltd is 10.1.11h5. Due to identified vulnerabilities in this version, it is required to upgrade the PAN-OS to version 10.1.14h9 to mitigate potential security risks and ensure system stability

DESIGN

There are no topology changes during the work done and after the work is done.

REQUIREMENT

Hardware Compatibility

Below is a link and screenshot which states that the Palo Alto Model 850 installed on Transcosmos Indonesia is compatible with PAN-OS version 10.1:

https://docs.paloaltonetworks.com/compatibility-matrix/supported-os-releases-by-model/palo-alto-networks-next-gen-firewalls

 

 

 

 

Upgrade Path:

The following is the upgrade path we took to upgrade PAN-OS from version 10.1.11h5. Upgrade to PAN-OS 10.1.11h5 as it is the latest version of 10.1.14h9.

AP-ID-JKTPAN01

&

AP-ID-JKTPAN0

2

Ver 10.1.11h5  10.1.14h9

Minimum Compatible Content and Software Version

Below is a link and screenshot that informs of the minimum version of Content and Software so that the upgrade process to PAN-OS 10.1.14h9 can be carried out:

https://docs.paloaltonetworks.com/pan-os/10-1/pan-os-release-notes/associated-content-and-software-versions/associated-content-and-software-versions-for-pan-os-10-1

When this document was created, the current version of the GlobalProtect App used was version 5.2 and the current Application and Threats Content Release was 8408.
